# Maintenance Report: SMI and DRE Results

## SMI Computation

The Software Maturity Index (SMI) is used to measure how stable the system became after maintenance. A higher SMI means that only a few modules were changed, added, or removed during maintenance, which indicates that the system is already stable.

Formula:

```text
SMI = [MT - (Fa + Fc + Fd)] / MT
```

Where:

```text
MT = total number of modules in the current version
Fa = number of modules added
Fc = number of modules changed
Fd = number of modules deleted
```

